### Banking Ledger API — HTTP scratch file for manual testing.
### Run `docker compose up -d` first, then `dotnet run --project src/BankingLedger.Api`.

@host = http://localhost:5259
@contentType = application/json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# ACCOUNTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Create an account with an initial balance
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "ownerName": "Alice",
  "initialBalance": 1000.00
}

### Get account by ID  (replace the GUID)
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

### Get balance
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/balance

### Get ledger (transaction history)
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/ledger

### Deposit
POST {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/deposit
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "amount": 250.00,
  "description": "Paycheck"
}

### Withdraw
POST {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/withdraw
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "amount": 100.00,
  "description": "Rent"
}

### Close account
POST {{host}}/api/accounts/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/close

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# TRANSFERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Transfer between two accounts
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "fromAccountId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "toAccountId":   "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
  "amount": 200.00,
  "description": "Rent split"
}

### Get transfer by ID
GET {{host}}/api/transfers/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099

### List all transfers
GET {{host}}/api/transfers

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# ACID DEMO ENDPOINTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### ATOMICITY — failed transfer rolls back both sides
POST {{host}}/api/demo/atomicity/failed-transfer

### CONSISTENCY — DB CHECK constraint blocks negative balance
POST {{host}}/api/demo/consistency/negative-balance

### ISOLATION — 10 concurrent withdrawals; only 3 succeed
POST {{host}}/api/demo/isolation/concurrent-withdrawals

### ISOLATION — 5 concurrent transfers; only 2 succeed
POST {{host}}/api/demo/isolation/concurrent-transfers

### DURABILITY — committed transfer survives
POST {{host}}/api/demo/durability/create-committed-transfer
